The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 December is 14,680 (1,699.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 December, there were 2,571 new confirmed cases (297.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 December, there were 1,312 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 96% (1,259 extra cases).
